==English==

===Pronunciation===
laz' yur ite

===Etymology===
Named for the distinctive blue coloration.

===Noun===
'''Lazurite'''
# A [[mineral]] of metamorphosed [[limestone]]s.  Lazurite forms the gemstone [[lapis lazuli]], and crushed lazurite provided the ''ultramarine'' color in artists' paint of the old masters.  [[sodalite]] and lazurite form the ''sodalite group'' of silicate minerals.

*Chemical composition: Sodium aluminum silicate with sulphur, <math>Na_{4-5}Al_3Si_3O_{12}S</math>

